label: localisation precision
detail: precision of the coordinate pair (precise or approximate)
notes: The precision is relative to the class of the Location. E.g., it is expected that if the coordinates have localisation precision "precise" and the class is “settlement”, the coordinates will fall within the area of the (medieval) settlement. But for a Location with class “house”, “precise” would mean that it is precisely localized at the granularity of houses! This means that a medieval house will rarely have localisation precision precise; rather, it will either be localized to the settlement, one of its gates or one of its parishes, and the localisation precision will be “approximate”, or there will be no coordinates but a location relation stating that the gate is “SRP next to” it or that the house has as its “superordinate location” the settlement. A church will often have localisation precision "precise", since its location is often known or it is still standing.

"comparuit" - probably summoned, if not even brought from prison. Even if I do not treat "comparuit" automatically as such - only if there is further indications.
Place of hearing: "Mediolani in burgo Porte Ticinensis foris"

label: Secundum dictum domine Bellacare uxoris domini Bonadei Karentani
notes: Self-defence that she did not remember previously => "denied" self-loop.
Chiaravalle abbot indirectly mentioned through Chiarvalle monastery paying the expenses.

label: Abiuratio et obligatio domine Stephane de Karentanis
Dictum Stephane de Karentanis
notes: She heard heresy from Andreas but claims not to have believed it. She went with Andreas to Chiaravalle even after the incident.

label: Abiuratio et obligatio Tarie de Pontariis et Bianche de Cerliano
Dictum suprascripte Tarie
notes: Visibly the first deposition - preceded with an abjuration and obligation.
The new question triggering defense of Guillelma when alive is visible here.
Ends up incriminating herself - does not deny that Guillelma is the Holy Spirit and "bene vellet quod Guillelma esset Spiritus sanctus".

label: Dictum Bianche de Cerliano
notes: Visibly the first deposition - preceded with an abjuration and obligation.
Unlike Taria, she does not incriminate herself, and she is not asked about Guillelma's own words or beliefs.
Unlike Taria, she does not throw suspicion on Franceschinus - perhaps protects him, being his familiaris.

label: Secundum dictum domine Felicis de Casate
Quoddam dictum domine Sibilie de Malcolçatis
notes: The wording suggests that she was not summoned: comparuit et dixit quod recordatur...

label: Abiuratio et obligatio domine Petre de Garbagnate
Abiuratio et obligatio Ottorini de Garbagnate
Quoddam dictum domine Sibilie de Malcolçatis
notes: "venit" - no mention of summons which often are mentioned, probably without summons.
Petra and Katella and Franceschinus incriminated as genuflecting and kissing the hand of Manfreda.

label: Quoddam dictum Andree Saramite
notes: "venit", no mentions of summons or escort; but mind the place of hearing (first appearance of this place) - already detained probably? (The evidence on him would warrant this.)

Guillelma in her life suspected for the first time - Andreas heard "from her or women who were there" a statement alluding to her 5 wounds (Christic identification) - but he still denies she said or alluded to be the Holy Spirit (p. 172). Nevertheless, at two spots, there is the marginal gloss "contra Guillelmam".
He must be detained by now (his detention - undated - mentioned incidentally at p. 240, on 1300-09-21).

label: Aliud dictum Andree
notes: He incriminates his deceased mother and sister as believing in Guillelma even after her abjuration.
The other crowd incriminated for signs of devotion towards Manfreda.

label: Dictum presbiteri Mirani
notes: Details on washing Guillelma's body and on the water preserved from this washing and used by Mayfreda to sign people.
"comparuit" => summoned (which also corresponds to this being answers to precise questions).

label: luramentum et obligatio domini Bonadei Karentani
Dictum suprascripti domini Bonadei
notes: "comparuit" => probably summoned, even if citatio not mentioned.
The names of "filius vel filie eius" supplied from Guglielmites Persons.
Seems to protect his family (and property?), but perhaps he really was not so much aware of what is going on.

label: Abiuratio et obligatio domine Iohanne uxoris Ambrosii de Massallia
Dictum predicte domine Iohanne
notes: Cites her mother as the source of her devotion for Guglielma but denies the Holy Spirit thing, thus even this is not an incrimination of her mother, just mention.
Probably summoned - "comparuit", and it seems that she is asked specific questions rather than appearing with info on her own.

label: Abiuratio et obligatio domine Iacobe uxoris Conradi de Coppa
Dictum suprascripte domine Iacobe
notes: Denies to have heard from Guillelma the Holy Spirit thing.
Denies believing in the Holy Spirit thing. Acknowledges only general devotion.
Probably summoned - "comparuit", and it seems that she is asked specific questions rather than appearing with info on her own.

label: Quoddam dictum sororis Mayfrede de Pirovano
notes: Asked, she says that the believers listened more to her than Andreas. She confirms her "plot" to hide the truth from inquisitors.
On the question about the source of Andreas' belief, she fails to incriminate Guglielma for this (which the inquisitors are checking now) - I put Guglielma as "denied".

label: Quoddam dictum Andree Saramite
notes: A decisive turn - he confirms that "fundamentum at originem predictorum errorum" he has from Guillelma herself.

label: Consilium sororis Iacobe de Nova
notes: No assessors really - it is legal experts who give advice.

Notary unclear - Beltramus not stated, probably him since this is his quaternus, but since the document type is special and under the archbishop's rather than inquisitor's authority, I leave unstated as the text does.

label: Quoddam dictum magistri Beltrami de Ferno
notes: Evidence of an attempted self-protection against inquisition - narrative about consultations to delegitimize the investigation that Beltramus was part of. No incrimination (in the sense of heretical involvement). Interestingly, no question on his already known Guglielmite allegiance asked - the inquisitors ask him only thematically on this attempt through legal means.

label: Dictum domine Dionese de Novate
notes: "constituta", but whether there was summons, is not said. Obligatio not recorded and not mentioned in the text, unlike in other cases - probably no pledge.
Acknowledges contribution to paramenta of Guillelma - but not a resurrected one => she "mentions" herself but does not incriminate herself.

label: Quoddam dictum Tarie de Pontariis
notes: She acknowledges having garments for the devotees, and Sibilla has them too (a recent thing - handed over the day before) - but no direct incrimination (i.e. some alleged illicit action), just potential source of suspicion.
Certainly summoned because asked "out of context" a specific question (garments for devotees).
Location = "ecclesia fratrum Predicatorum" - certainly S. Eustorgius.

label: Quoddam dictum magistri Beltrami de Ferno
notes: Denies being at a mass celebrated by Manfreda but acknowledges having heard that it took place and that Manfreda warned them not to talk about the mass "quia ego et Andreas Saramita essemus mortui".
Certainly summoned since asked to answer specific questions rather than coming with info of his own.

label: Quoddam dictum domine Sibilie Malconçati
notes: A crucial testimony on Manfreda's mass actually happening.
Her own involvement implied by her describing the mass.

She involves Guillelma through Andreas' words as a source of heresy - even if this is through Andreas' words, it is incriminating in the logic of how the trial evolves, so Guillelma I think is to be considered incriminated.

label: Dictum domine Dionese de Novate
notes: "rediit" - unclear whether summoned, cf. Sibilia coming the same day "sponte sua" (preceding document).

label: Quoddam dictum Aydeline de Crimella
notes: The participants feast in the house of the Novate summarized as "predicti et predicte, quos et quas suprascripta domina Dionese dixit..." - I take over the list and - of course - add Dionese; same for the other feast.

label: Quoddam dictum Francischi de Garbagnate
notes: Incriminates Guillelma for having said that since 1262 will be sacrified not Corpus Christi but the body of the Holy Spirit which is herself. Important testimony.
"venit", and no mention of obligatio (and obligatio not present) - I infer that he was not required to make a pledge now, and thus it also seems he was not summoned.

Visibly not the first deposition, alludes to "remembering" something (i.e. what was not said at a previous deposition) - at least second. But not in the extant register - so I put it as first in a series of the extant ones.

label: Abiuratio et obligatio domine Ricadone uxoris quondam Andree Saramite
Dictum predicte domine Ricadone
notes: Questions the testimony from Andreas and Flordebellina against herself - defends herself (successfully, it turns out). Follows an inquiry about Andreas' property (wine).

label: Quoddam dictum Alegrantie de Perusiis
notes: Dinner in the house of Iacobus de Ferno. Testimony on hearing Guillelma = Holy Spirit ca. 24 years ago, i.e. around 1276, and Guillelma denying this (either this is historical, or it is a defence of Guillellma herself, in any case it makes sense - the inquisitors ask about "when" exactly because they are attempting at incriminating Guillelma.

Manfreda's socia, humiliata from Biassono, mentioned in this and several other depositions without name. Carabella thinks (just thinks; p. 246) that it was Flordebellina - supplied for this anonymous Humiliata in all depositions.
"comparuit", but gives new information and no question recorded - probably not summoned.

label: Quoddam dictum magistri Iacobi de Ferno
notes: On the feast in his house (house of Iacobus de Ferno).
In addition to Alegrantia, he mentions Amiço.
Citatus - explicitly mentioned. Strangely, pledge not mentioned in the text and not extant in the register - probably not required (social standing?).
Interestingly, the gloss marks "contra Guillelmam et Mayfredam" where the word is cited on M. saying that G. commissioned her to tell them the Holy Spirit thing.

label: Abiuratio et obligatio Stephani de Crimella
Dictum Stephani de Crimella
notes: Dinner in the house of Iacobus de Ferno.

Gives the highest number (15). Agrees on Amiço being here, and adds Marchixius Sichus and presbiter Guillelmus and Bellacara (p. 234); was she there? Should we take the maximum list? Was Guillelmus, not named by Iacobus de Ferno and Alegrantia, actually at the announcement and not just at the dinner before ("traxerunt se et intraverunt quamdam cameram", p. 234)?

Exculpates himself - says he disagreed and was sent outside of the room, so I consider him as denying his involvement (but he includes himself in the list of those present). However, at two spots the inquisitors mark "contra se ipsum" - when he acknowledges that after that he was at several feasts and went to Guillelma's grave with Andreas and others - reading this, I came back and put Stephanus also among the incriminated, not just denied - i.e. he is in the category of partially defended.

label: Abiuratio et obligatio ser Danisii Cotte
Dictum ser Danisii Cotte
notes: Dinner in the house of Iacobus de Ferno.

Does not mention Marchixius Sichus and Guillelmus and Bellacara - Stephanus de Crimella's list is probably too maximalistic (but he is not the only one who mentions Bellacara - also Aydelina does at p. 242). He acknowledges to have been there but denies Mayfreda's presence (less to protect her - she is burned by now - than to protect himself and possibly others present); I also put Flordebellina among protected, even if not explicitly - he misses what the others say, i.e. the socia, whom thanks to Carabella p. 246 we know to be Flordebellina. He only speaks about bona verba, denies any Holy Spirit thing. Speaks about the legacy of Guillelma to meet and love one another, whence the meeting, but the Holy Spirit thing he claims to have heard only after Andreas's detention.

label: Quoddam dictum Aydeline
notes: Dinner in the house of Iacobus de Ferno.

Somewhat different list - as with her husband, she includes Guillelmus presbiter and Marchixius Sichus and Bellacara and Iohanna - just like her husband. She names her husband among those present but testifies to his refusal of the Holy Spirit thing, i.e. fails to incriminate him (if not for not reporting it). By contrast, she incriminates herself heavily - acknowledges she was the first to agree with Manfreda's statement.
Comparuit, summons not mentioned here (unlike in some previous concerning the dinner). Oath mentioned but pledge not and not found, so I impute not.
The inquisitor considers Guillelma to be incriminated by Mayfreda's words about G. sending her to tell them the Holy Spirit thing - "contra Guillelmam et sororem Mayfredam" marked in margine.

label: Quoddam dictum domine Carabelle de Toscanis
notes: Dinner in the house of Iacobus de Ferno, then evidence on Franceschinus M. and others singing a song for Guillelma.

The list of participants in the dinner includes Bellacara and states Flordebellina, but just that she thinks so. On that basis, imputed for the unnamed humiliata from Biassono also in the other depositions.

Second deposition, since it mentions: "si ipsa fuisset recordata de predictis, quando alia vice fuit coram inquisitore suprascripto, dixisset et confessa fuisset omnia que modo dixit, sed tunc non recordabatur de predictis" (p. 248).

label: Quoddam dictum ser Danisii Cotte
notes: Dinner in the house of Iacobus de Ferno; he says he has remembered about Manfreda and her companion thanks to Alegrantia who reminded him.
Acknowledges the talk in the room now, incl. the Holy Spirit thing. Interestingly, the text stresses that all who were at the dinner were in the room later (p. 250).

Gives a list of believers in the Holy Spirit thing back then - Andreas, Manfreda, Aydelina, Amiço, Bellacara. Does not list himself - holds that he only heard it after Andreas' detection and the dinner was an exception, the only other occasion.
He says that years ago he heard from Iacobus de Ferno that there will soon be a big celebration (beginnings of Guglielmite ideas on her resurrection?).
Interesting citation of Manfreda: "Vos omnes comeditis de uno pane et bibitis de uno vino sed non estis omnes de uno corde et una voluntate."

label: Quoddam dictum Francischi de Garbagnate
notes: Asked to comment on some writing of his. Explicitly incriminates Guillelma as converting Andreas: "primo instructus fuit ab ipsa Guillelma in credentia predictorum errorum" (p. 254).
Lists those of the belief: long list ,and partly original, people who have not yet appeared - apparently a valuable list of inner circle generation 1!
Claims to have come 2 weeks before but Guido not wanting to hear him and saying he knows all this.
Carabella asks him to sing a Guglielmite hymn.

label: Relatio Balçarri de Monteorfano servitoris officii inquisitionis
Absolutio facta per inquisitorem domine Sibilie de Malconçatis
Abiuratio et obligatio dominarum Catelle et Petre de Oldegardis
Quoddam dictum fratris Girardi de Novaçano
notes: Asked whether Guillelma said anything against the Catholic faith, he avoids the question, and asked whether at least Andreas told him she did allude to this, he said he does not know - either protects Guillelma or protects.
Denies to have ever believed in the Holy Spirit thing. Still remains outside - but forced to acknowledge several points that he failed to depose in front of Lanfranchus 4 years ago.

Confirms a previous list of believers, of whom only Andreas, Albertonus is cited here (p. 270) - it is from a previous deposition in front of Lanfranchus inquisitor 4 years ago, does not belong here among those incriminated.

label: Quoddam dictum Stephani de Crimella
notes: Called to just answer whether he knew Aydelina went to Chiaravalle celebrations after he reprimanded her at the feast in the house of Iacobus de Ferno; he says he knew and did not forbid this to her. Since this can sound as the official cult, I put nobody as incriminated, but it is not a strategy of protection / denial either, so goes into mentioned.

label: Quoddam dictum fratris Girardi de Novaçano
notes: Called to answer the question whether Cara, his wife, went to Chiaravalle celebrations; confirms and says he did not forbid this but warned her not to believe in the Holy Spirit thing.

He does not really incriminate himself, even if strictly speaking he names others, as he acknowledges explicitly, because they went to Chiaravalle, and he went with them - but phrased in such a way that it is not really a self-incrimination. Cara is mentioned, not really incriminated even if the inquisitors start to ask about the time aspect and whether after those husbands knew, they let their wifes go to Chiaravalle - but the process then stopped and Chiaravalle came out clean in the end.

Asked to name those "de credentia et devotione illius Guillelme", he provides a long and probably overstated list in the sense that he gives even Stephanus de Crimella and the sacristan Ubertinus etc., but broadly his list is confirmed elsewhere, just Miranus Roxa and Ubertinus the sacristan and Stephanus are not part of the inner circle.

label: Quoddam dictum ser Danisii Cotte civitatis Mediolani Porte Nove
notes: Summary of previous deposition supplemented with the question of who was the believer then - Andreas, Manfreda, Aydelina, Amiço, Bellacara.
Still denies his belief in the Holy Spirit thing - then or now.
Provides major evidence on Guillelma saying that she is born from a man and a wife - i.e. a human (probably still attempts to protect her memory).

label: Quoddam dictum Stephani de Crimella
notes: Just asked why he shouted at his wife at the feast in Iacobus de Ferno's house, says that because he believed that this is heretical.
I do not count this as a new incrimination of his wife; it is a targetted question on him, rather.

label: Absolutio excomunicationis dominarum Catelle et Petre de Oldegardis
notes: This is an absolution. It contains a summary of guilt ("culpa") which yields the names of Andreas and Manfreda, but since this is a summary of an extant dictum and is not made at a deposition, I do not mark this as new accusation.

label: Licencia data magistro Iacobo de Ferno deponendi cruces
notes: Interesting to see his son Beltramus de Ferno, also implicated, acting as witness.

label: Preceptum factum per inquisitorem magistro Iacobo de Ferno
Licencia data fratri Girardo de Novaçano deponendi cruces
Preceptum factum fratri Girardo de Novaçano
notes: Order to pay libras XXV tertiolorum.

label: Licencia data Stephano de Crimella deponendi cruces
Licencia deponendi cruces data Aydeline uxori Stephani de Crimella
Preceptum factum Aydeline uxori Stephani de Crimella
notes: Order to pay libras XXV tertiolorum.

label: Licencia deponendi cruces data domine Dionese de Novate
Preceptum factum per inquisitorem domine Dionese de Novate
notes: Order to pay libras XXV tertiolorum.

label: Licencia deponendi cruces data per inquisitorem domine Flori et Tarie
Precepta facta per inquisitorem domine Flori et Tarie
notes: Order to pay libras XXV tertiolorum.

label: Confessio facta per inquisitorem fratri Girardo de Novaçano
Confessio facta per inquisitorem domine Dionese de Novate
Primum dictum sororis Mayfrede de Pirovano
notes: This deposition is lost. It was recorded by Manfredus de Cera, i.e. in another folder. Summarized in her third deposition, incl. the name of the inquisitor and notary. Probably she did not give much there. Place and witnesses not stated.

Date: "die martis .XVIIII. mensis aprilis" corrected by Benedetti to ".XVIII" (correction noted in the apparatus, without justification), but there is no reason for this, since 19 April 1300 actually was a Tuesday. Moreover, the same date "die martis .XVIIII. mensis aprilis" again given for this deposition at p. 192.

label: Absolutio domine Ricadone de Saramitis Sr. per Mayfredum de Dovaria
notes: Also mentioned p. 176: "si postquam ipsa domina Ricadona mater sua abiuravit omnem heresim coram fratre Mayfredo de Dovaria".

label: Absolutio Melioris de Saramitis Sr. per Mayfredum de Dovaria
Dictum Bellacare Karentane coram Mayfredo de Dovaria
Citatio Bellacare Karentane per Mayfredum de Dovaria
Citatio Flordebelline de Saramitis per Mayfredum de Dovaria
Citatio Andree Saramite per Mayfredum de Dovaria
Citatio Iacobe de Nova per Mayfredum de Dovaria
Dictum Flordebelline de Saramitis coram Mayfredo de Dovaria
Dictum Melioris de Saramitis coram Mayfredo de Dovaria
Dictum Iacobe de Nova coram Mayfredo de Dovaria
Dictum Andree Saramite coram Mayfredo de Dovaria
Dictum Iacobi de Ferno
notes: This is cited as a plural: "de quibus facta est mentio in aliis dictis huius testis", but it can also be one deposition. Probably, this is a recent deposition in this investigation, i.e. it could be part of the lost documents by Mayfredus de Cera, but I will not impute either the date or the notary.

label: Abiuratio Mayfrede de Pirovano in manibus Mayfredi de Dovaria
Abiuratio Girardi de Novaçano in manibus inquisitorum
Dictum Andree Saramite scriptum per Mayfredum de Cera
Prima abiuratio et obligatio Franceschini Malconçati
Abiuratio Bellacare Karentane in manibus Mayfredi de Dovaria
notes: "si audivit ab aliqua persona postquam iuravit coram fratre Mayfredo de Dovaria": probably this means abjuration.

label: Abiuratio Andree Saramite in manibus Mayfredi de Dovaria
Dictum Carabelle de Toschanis
notes: "si ipsa fuisset recordata de predictis, quando alia vice fuit coram inquisitore suprascripto, dixisset et confessa fuisset omnia que modo dixit, sed tunc non recordabatur de predictis" (p. 248).
I presume it was in the lost part by Mayfredus de Cera.
